rComments: Good prof. Lectures and examples are clear and helpful. Very nice too.

Professor Tassone is a very good choice for RSM 219. This is a fundamental course in Rotman (pre-requisite for almost everything), so having the right prof is important. He is a very clear speaker and is helpful if you have any questions. He is a fair grader (B average) and genuinely cares about his students. Would definitely recommend him.

he really cares about you and makes the class very comfortable in his discussions. He is very clear and one of the few professors that I talk to frequently. He wants you to understand the material and I would hands-down take him again for any other course

Prof Tassone is kind and listens to your questions. Definately made RSM219 better. The course is heavy on the textbook readings though. The prof integrated real world examples into the lectures to aid with understanding the course objectives.

nice guy, rambles on a times, not the head of the course so not that clear on what to expect on tests. If you attend a decent amount and answer some questions, participation will be 100%. The slides are directly from the textbook.

He's a pretty good lecturer; his classes are quite useful if you don't feel like reading the textbook. The lectures follow the textbook material very closely, so they are alternatives. He also is quite responsive to questions and is easy to understand.
Just read the book and you're good. He's pretty good a teaching too. Gonna take his first test today.
